Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Instance 1: Constructs Involved: Search Podcasts, Parse Search Query, include relationship from "Search Podcasts" to "Parse Search Query"
   Instance 1: Explanation: "Parse Search Query" is an inclusion use case included only by "Search Podcasts." It is not associated with any actor, does not include or extend any other use case, is not extended by any use case, and is not involved in any generalization. "Parse Search Query" does not represent a complete service observable to any user — it is merely a decomposed internal step of the search functionality. This constitutes Functional Decomposition via the include relationship.

